{
  "comment_text": {
    "sn22.156:1.2": "“Theory of self” (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>attānudiṭṭhi</i>) is not a defined technical term. <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Anudiṭḥi</i> is used for developed “theories” (eg. <a href='https://suttacentral.net/dn1/en/sujato'>DN 1</a> throughout), and this holds true for “theory of self” (<a href='https://suttacentral.net/dn15/en/sujato#24.12'>DN 15:24.12</a>), especially the Upaniṣadic view (<a href='https://suttacentral.net/snp5.16/en/sujato#4.3'>Snp 5.16:4.3</a>). "
  },
